  "title": "Regulatory Affairs (Pharmacist)",
  "description": "<p>Our client is a <strong>provides temperature-controlled logistics for the global pharmaceutical and biotech industries.</strong> Due to business needs, they are now recruiting a Regulatory Affairs to be part of their Team for ongoing transformation projects. They are located in the <strong>West </strong>- easily accessible.</p><p><strong>Responsibilities:</strong></p><ul><li>Implement and maintain the Quality Management System (QMS), including Quality Risk Management, Corrective and Preventive Actions (CAPA), and Change Control processes</li><li>Review and approve material batches as required.</li><li>Develop, write, and authorize QMS documentation.</li><li>Collect, analyze, and report quality metrics.</li><li>Conduct internal and external audits to ensure compliance.</li><li>Deliver training and guidance on QMS, as well as Good Manufacturing Practices (GMP) and Good Distribution Practices (GDP).</li><li>Serve as the primary company liaison during client and regulatory audits, providing timely audit responses and documentation as needed.</li></ul><p><em>Interested candidates who wish to apply for the advertised position, please click </em><em><strong>APPLY NOW</strong></em><em> or email an updated copy of your resume/cv.</em><br /><em>We regret that only shortlisted candidate will be notified.</em><br /><br /><em>Email Address: </em><a href=\"mailto:jobs@recruitpedia.sg\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"><em>jobs@recruitpedia.sg</em></a></p><p><em>Recruitpedia Pte. Ltd.</em><br /><em>EA License No: 19C9682</em><br /><em>EA Personnel No: R25157233 (Loh Pooi Keng)</em></p>",
